			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<span class="time"><strong>Want Genesis games, without the Genesis? Read on.</strong></span>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#606B73" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Sega has teamed up with Real Networks (Real Player) to make a program called RealOne Arcade Player (or maybe Sega is just a huge supporter). <br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.sega.com/games/pc/segaclassics.jhtml?dm=?dm=fpheadlinenews" target="_blank">http://www.sega.com/games/pc/segacl...=fpheadlinenews</a><br />
<br />
Here, you'll find FREE downloads of several classic Genesis games. Just click that link, and click &quot;FREE DOWNLOAD&quot; of the game of your choice. It will download the RealOne program, and that particular game. Then, from inside the program, you can download the other games without the RealOne installation. This includes several Sega Classics, as well as other non-Sega games. <br />
<br />
There is a catch. You download the full version of the game, and get 60 minutes of total playime. Then, if you wish, you may purchase the full game. Also, I think they could have knocked off five bucks on most of those titles, only one or two are worth that price now. <br />
<br />
Here is the SEGA game list currently supported by this program. (full-game prices in parentheses) <br />
<br />
-Sonic ($9.99) <br />
-Sonic 2 ($14.99) <br />
-Toejam and Earl($14.99) <br />
-Shinobi III($14.99) <br />
-Ecco the Dolphin($14.99) <br />
-Vectorman($14.99) <br />
-Columns 3($14.99) <br />
-Dr. Robotnik's Mean Bean Machine($14.99) <br />
-Phantasy Star 2(($14.99) <br />
<br />
<br />
- Virtua Fighter 2 (Coming Soon, and this is the 2D Genesis version, not the good version, so don't get your hopes up) <br />
<br />
I've played Sonic 1 and PS2 so far. I will say this, there are no noticeable Genesis Emulation problems here. PERFECT sound, and NEAR-PERFECT video. I say near Perfect, because in Sonic, something didn't seem right. I can't put my finger on it, but maybe someone else can catch it. <br />
<br />
I think If Sega releases the rest of the PS games, some Shining Force games, and gets some third parties in on this (Gunstar Heroes...drool...), I'll be hooked. <br />
<br />
Also, Real Networks should try to get the SNES in on this (though I doubt it will happen, Nintendo would rather re-release on GBA and charge full-price again).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
